    <h2>Step 1: Understand the Structure</h2>
    <p>
      A haiku consists of three lines with a syllable pattern of 5-7-5 (totaling 17 syllables).
    </p>
    <h2>Step 2: Choose a Theme</h2>
    <p>
      Focus on a moment from nature or an emotion that you want to convey in your poem.
    </p>
    <h2>Step 3: Use Vivid Imagery</h2>
    <p>
      Craft each line with descriptive language, painting a clear picture in the reader's mind. 
      Revise and refine to make every word count.
    </p>
    <h2>Step 4: Read Aloud</h2>
    <p>
      Ensure your haiku flows smoothly and evokes the intended feelings by reading it aloud.
    </p>
    <h2>Step 5: Share and Enjoy</h2>
    <p>
      Share your haiku with others and appreciate the beauty of this concise and expressive poetic form.
    </p>
